question:
What tool design would allow TIAMAT to programmatically extract and annotate relevant web data from aiagentsdirectory.com, using a novel combination of natural language processing (NLP) and web scraping techniques, and return a JSON-formatted dataset containing:

1. Annotated web pages with identified AI-related content (e.g., job postings, research papers, AI tool announcements) with confidence scores (0-1);
2. Extracted entity mentions (e.g., people, organizations, technologies) with corresponding URLs and timestamps;
3. Identified relationships between extracted entities and web pages, with associated weights and confidence scores;

This tool should integrate with existing tools like search_web, fetch_web, and expose_port, and be deployable as a standalone application or a series of API endpoints.
